dismissalText.commentary: Aiden Markram c Mathews b AM Fernando 9 (11b 2x4 0x6 14m) SR: 81.81

dismissalComment.html: Edged and taken! Asitha strikes and roars. This is what he was working on and that shape away from the right-hander comes to his air. He lands it on a length - slightly shorter perhaps - just outside off, Markram feels for it and hangs his bat out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes low to first slip, where Mathews makes no mistake. Markram back with a low score and Sri Lanka draw first blood

dismissalText.commentary: Tony de Zorzi c PHKD Mendis b MVT Fernando 4 (9b 1x4 0x6 16m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: Terrific catch from Kamindu and Vishwa is on the board now. Almost a mirror image of the Markram dismissal. He lands it on a length just outside off, forcing de Zorzi to poke at it. He gets squared up and gets a thick outside edge that flies low to the right of second slip. Kamindu dives and pouches it with both hands. Two wickets after opting to bowl, Sri Lanka making the right noises

dismissalText.commentary: Tristan Stubbs c Karunaratne b Kumara 16 (38b 3x4 0x6 60m) SR: 42.1

dismissalComment.html: Kumara makes amends after a 17-run first over. Gets rid of Stubbs. Sharp back of a length ball shaping away from Stubbs just outside off. He pokes at it, gets a thick outside edge to Karunaratne at third slip. The ball bursts through his hands, but he manages to nestle it between his legs. Big, big wicket for SL just as Stubbs and Bavuma were looking to dig in

dismissalComment.html: And just like that Bavuma is gone! Just minutes before lunch, the SA skipper has thrown it away. Looks to swipe this across the line and gets a top edge that sails straight up. dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews lbw b Jansen 25 (42b 2x4 0x6 46m) SR: 59.52

dismissalComment.html: Rapped on the pads, and it looks to be plumb. Mathews has a word with Chandimal and opts for the DRS. Jansen changes angle and goes around the wicket and lands it on a length, slanting into the batter. He looks to defend it in front of his body but is beaten on the inside due to the angle. Hit on the knee-roll of the front pad. Is the angle taking it down? It is given out, so South Africa just need an umpire's call to continue their celebration, and it is three reds on the Ball-Tracker! Mathews falls and takes a review with him

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal c & b Coetzee 83 (174b 12x4 0x6 295m) SR: 47.7

dismissalComment.html: South Africa should forget jaffas and just hoover up softies! The first wicket of the day - of a half-centurion - was a lobbed-up flick to midwicket, this - the second one is a lobbed flick back to the bowler. Quite the roar from Coetzee as he thunders down to the ground, throws the ball up after taking the catch around head-height, to his right. 131ks ball on a three-quarter length, on the pads. Chandimal, who was all set, went for the flick, but was too early on the shot. Shows the day-four pitch can't be trusted. Gets a leading edge, is denied a century

dismissalComment.html: Jansen gets his tenth for the match! The length is perfect this time, has Mendis unsure whether to play on the front or the back foot. With the line being around fifth-stump, he wanted to play it late and steer it to third again. But the around-the-wicket angle did him in. It was closer than he expected, the bat was windscreen-wiped indecisively. The edge was taken to the keeper. Jansen is pumped!
